snippet.textDisplay: To be honest, the lyrical phrasing here doesn’t really complement the music. It feels less like songwriting and more like prose being recited over an instrumental. Good lyrics should lock into the rhythm and dynamics of the track—matching its cadence, rises, and pauses—so that words and music move together like parts of the same instrument. The instrumentation is solid, but the vocal delivery and poetic structure feel out of sync, which breaks the overall flow
